genresAdvancedInfo.name: rap norteno chileno
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Rap norteno chileno is a subgenre of rap music that originated in the northern regions of Chile. It is characterized by its social and political commentary, often addressing issues such as poverty, inequality, and corruption. The music is typically accompanied by traditional Chilean instruments such as the charango and the quena.
